title: Ohio's 9th congressional district - Wikipedia
snippet: Ohio's 9th congressional district has been represented by Representative Marcy Kaptur (D) since 1983.

title: Ohio's 9th Congressional District - Ballotpedia
snippet: Steven Kraus (R) defeated Keith Colton (R) and W. Benjamin Franklin (R) in the Republican primary for U.S. House Ohio District 9 on May 8, 2018. ... Heading into the election, Ballotpedia rated this race as safely Democratic. Incumbent Marcy Kaptur (D) defeated Donald Philip Larson (R) in the general election. Kaptur was unopposed in the Democratic primary. Larson defeated Steven Kraus and Joel Lieske in the Republican primary on March 15, 2016.[1] See also: Ohio's 9th Congressional District elections, 2014
